---
import TechnologyLayout from '../../layouts/TechnologyLayout.astro';
import TextSection from '../../components/content/TextSection.astro';
import SectionWrapper from '../../components/ui/SectionWrapper.astro';
import WhenToChoose from '../../components/content/WhenToChoose.astro';
---

<TechnologyLayout
  title="Looker | Nimzo Data"
  description="Looker and LookML implementation on BigQuery — semantic layer design, governed metrics, dashboards, and access control."
  toolName="Looker"
  toolCategory="Business Intelligence"
  heroPositioning="Looker is the most powerful BI tool in the GCP ecosystem — we implement it for companies that need a centralized semantic layer and are ready to invest accordingly."
>
  <TextSection title="What It Is" bg="white">
    <p>Looker is Google's enterprise BI platform, built around LookML — a modeling language that defines a governed semantic layer sitting between your data warehouse and your end users. Every metric, dimension, and relationship is defined once in LookML and reused consistently across all reports and dashboards.</p>
  </TextSection>

  <TextSection title="Why We Chose It" bg="white">
    <p>For organizations where data governance and metric consistency matter — where finance and product can't have different definitions of 'revenue' — Looker is the right tool. The LookML semantic layer also makes Looker uniquely powerful for embedded analytics and multi-tenant reporting. The GCP native integration (Looker is now part of Google Cloud) also means tighter BigQuery integration, including BI Engine acceleration.</p>
  </TextSection>

  <TextSection title="How We Use It" bg="white">
    <ul class="how-list">
      <li>Design and implement LookML models: views, explores, derived tables, and measures</li>
      <li>Build executive and operational dashboards with governed metrics</li>
      <li>Implement user access controls and group-level permissions</li>
      <li>Configure Looker's BigQuery connection with persistent derived tables (PDTs) for performance</li>
      <li>Set up scheduled Looks and dashboard delivery for regular stakeholder reporting</li>
      <li>Advise on Looker vs. Lightdash vs. Steep for greenfield BI decisions</li>
    </ul>
  </TextSection>

  <SectionWrapper bg="white" py="lg">
    <WhenToChoose
      title="When Looker is the right BI tool — and when it isn't"
      blocks={[
        {
          heading: 'Choose Looker when:',
          bullets: [
            'You need enterprise governance and consistent metrics across teams',
            'You have 20+ BI users',
            'You want embedded analytics or multi-tenant reporting',
            "You need LookML's full semantic layer capabilities",
          ],
          note: 'Budget: €3,000–€6,000+/month for Looker Core.',
        },
        {
          heading: 'Choose Lightdash instead when:',
          bullets: [
            "You're already on dbt (metrics live in dbt YAML)",
            'Team is 5–20 users',
            'Budget is €500–€2,000/month',
            "You don't need the full LookML semantic layer",
          ],
        },
        {
          heading: 'Choose Steep instead when:',
          bullets: [
            'Primary users are non-technical',
            'The goal is broad self-service access for business users',
            'Budget is under €500/month',
          ],
        },
      ]}
    />
  </SectionWrapper>
</TechnologyLayout>

<style>
  .how-list {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .how-list li { margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .how-list li::marker { color: var(--color-primary); }
</style>
